<!--
  head.ejs — HTML shell loaded by every page (via include('head'))
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  CDN dependencies loaded here (all pages pay this cost):
    • Bootstrap 5.1.3 CSS + JS bundle
    • jQuery 3.5.1
    • Material Icons + Outlined
    • Yusei Magic Google Font

  Local stylesheets (load order matters — style.css wins on conflicts):
    universal.css → progress.css → dragula.css → customIcons.css → style.css

  REMOVED (were dead weight):
    • jQuery UI 1.13.2 CSS — JS was never loaded, CSS alone did nothing.
    • js-cookie 2.x — never used; script.js has its own getCookieObject().

  AUDIT NOTES:
    • No CSP <meta> or nonce on scripts — all inline <script> blocks work but
      there's no Content Security Policy protection.
    • No <body> tag — each page view must open its own <body>.
    • Bootstrap 5.1.3 is ~2 major versions behind (current is 5.3.x).
-->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US" translate="no">
